      <section id="introduction">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          HTML, or <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, is the backbone of the web.
          It defines the structure and content of every webpage we use.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="history">
        <h2>2. A Brief History</h2>
        <p>
          HTML was invented by Tim Berners-Lee in 1989. Its original purpose was to share documents
          at CERN. Since then, it has evolved dramatically.
        </p>

        <figure>
          <img src="early-web.png" alt="Screenshot of the first web browser" width="400" />
          <figcaption>The first web browser: a window into the past.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <blockquote>
          "The Web as I envisaged it, we have not seen it yet. The future is still so much bigger than the past."
          <cite> — Tim Berners-Lee</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section id="today">
        <h2>3. HTML Today</h2>
        <p>
          Modern HTML supports multimedia, responsive design, accessibility, and more. It’s no longer
          just about text — it's about interaction and experience.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>

